goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites?
goals.rationale: A box plot will show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield data, giving a good idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.rationale: A grouped bar chart will allow for easy comparison of the yield of different varieties of barley, showing any significant differences or similarities.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and nitrogen level?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield vs nitrogen level
goals.rationale: A scatter plot will show the relationship between yield and nitrogen level, allowing for the identification of any trends or patterns in the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Stacked bar chart of yield by site
goals.rationale: A stacked bar chart will show the total yield at each site, as well as the contribution of each variety to the total yield, allowing for easy comparison of the yield across different sites.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield for each variety?
goals.rationale: A histogram will show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for the identification of any skewness or outliers in the data.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='yield', data=data, ax=ax, color='lightblue')
    ax.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["yield"].mean():.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['variety']).mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='variety', y='yield', data=data)
    plt.title('How does the yield of different varieties of barley compare?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['site', 'year']).agg({'yield': 'sum'}).reset_index()
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='site', y='yield', hue='year', data=data, palette='muted')
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['yield', 'variety']]
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='variety', multiple='stack', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield for each variety?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
